<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-bZiX9Qne2KY/T2o1JrTi82I/AAAAAAAAAeQ/1mEs-H6ZiKQ/s1600/IMG_5312.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" height="400" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-bZiX9Qne2KY/T2o1JrTi82I/AAAAAAAAAeQ/1mEs-H6ZiKQ/s400/IMG_5312.jpg" width="265" /></a></div>

One of the finished upstairs company rooms.  The company rooms were  furnished by the individual 10-man companies of the regiment, each in a  different style to the taste of the company.

<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/-7k4kIsqlMo0/T2o1K4McagI/AAAAAAAAAes/B0W4Qj-vURo/s1600/IMG_5355.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" height="266" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/-7k4kIsqlMo0/T2o1K4McagI/AAAAAAAAAes/B0W4Qj-vURo/s400/IMG_5355.jpg" width="400" /></a></div>

 The renovators chose to leave imperfections in the walls and ceilings rather than paint over them.

